"v.使燃烧；激怒(某人) 【英】 v. 使燃烧(to set on fire)；激怒(某人)( excite intensely with anger) 【考】 反义词：assuage(缓 和); subdue(征服) v. 激起(强烈的感情, 如: 愤怒); 使(组织或器官)发炎; 点燃 【记】flame(n 火焰; 热情; 激情); inflamed(adj 发炎的; 红肿的); 【参】inflammable(adj 易燃的; 易怒的) 【反】assuage(vt 缓和; 镇定); subdue(v 征服) 【记】in, en 使 + flame 燃烧 inflame (v.)  mid-14c., ""to set on fire with passion,"" from Latin inflammare ""to set on fire, kindle,"" figuratively ""to rouse, excite,"" from in- ""in"" (see in- (2)) + flammare ""to flame,"" from flamma ""flame"" (see flame (n.)). Literal sense of ""to cause to burn"" first recorded in English late 14c."
